The paper discusses a specific family of arithmetic coders and their unique property of symmetry between encoder and decoder, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the efficiency of encoding and decoding on different computing architectures, which falls under the categories of data structures (cs.DS), distributed computing (cs.DC), and programming languages (cs.PL).
